N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 150.2 - Legibility and riders

State Regulations

The department shall decline to file any document that is not
legible because the paper weight, ink color, font size, type face, extraneous
marks, file format or other quality impairs the ability to make an official
record. Documents shall contain no riders other than tax consents and official
certificates. Notes
